=Install Windows 7 on the Cr-48= 

----
# ====Install the Insyde H2O BIOS by following the [[Flash BIOS|instructions here]][[image:cr48windows7.jpg width="400" height="415" align="right"]]==== 
# ====Boot and immediately press → (F2) to enter BIOS setup. Confirm the following settings are correct in the BIOS:==== 
** Advanced > IDE Configuration > HDC Configured As <AHCI>
** Power > Advanced CPU Control > HT Support <Auto>
** Boot > ACPI Selection <Acpi 3.0> (4.0 works also, but the BIOS says use 1.0 or 3.0)
# ====Obtain a copy of [[@http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00GOUBT6E/ref=as_li_qf_sp_asin_il_tl?ie=UTF8&camp=1789&creative=9325&creativeASIN=B00GOUBT6E&linkCode=as2&tag=mcdotechserv-20|Windows 7]]. Both 32 and 64-bit versions will work. After installation you may have limited usable disk space unless you [[Install Larger SSD|install a larger SSD]].==== 
# ====On another computer, create a bootable Windows 7 installation USB drive or SD card using the [[file:cr-48/Windows7-USB-DVD-tool.exe|Windows 7 USB DVD Tool available here]]==== 
# ====Insert the USB drive or SD card in the Cr-48 and boot to the Windows 7 installer. During the installation:==== 
** Select "Custom Install" rather than "Upgrade"
** Select "Drive options (advanced)" and delete every partition on the internal Solid-State Drive (SSD)
** Install Windows to 'Disk 0 Unallocated Space'
# ====After Windows finishes installing, remove the installation media and reboot. The reboot may happen automatically - be sure to remove the installation media to boot properly from the SSD - don't restart the installation process.==== 
